abstract: TALLMAN, N. Y., Oct. 27 -Up Jumps The Devil, owned and handled by Frank West, won two championships by the narrowest of margins yesterday at the Cherry Lane Stables horse show.

abstract: WEST POINT, N.Y., Oct. 25 -- Lynn Moore, Army's captain, burst through the Boston College line and ran 82 yards for a touchdown on the first scrimmage play today, setting a pattern of individual and team excellence unmatched by the cadets this season as they went on to a 38-7 victory.
headline_main: Army, Tallying on First Play, Conquers Boston College, 38-7
headline_print_headline: Army, Tallying on First Play, Conquers Boston College, 38-7
